# Electron preload and main

- Expose renderer capabilities only through `contextBridge` in `electron-preload.ts` as `window.faContentBridgeAPIs` properties.
- Implement API objects in `src-electron/contentBridgeAPIs/`; extend `src/globals.d.ts` + `types/I_*.ts` on shape changes.
- **IPC channel names**: shared main ↔ preload strings in `electron-ipc-bridge.ts` as grouped `export const` objects. Preload `ipcRenderer.invoke` + main `ipcMain.handle` import from that file — names cannot drift. Register in `mainScripts/ipcManagement/register*Ipc.ts`, invoke at startup (`startApp()` in `mainScripts/appManagement.ts`; follow `registerFaWindowControlIpc` / `registerFaUserSettingsIpc`). Main `electron-store` for `faUserSettings` in `mainScripts/userSettings/` (`userSettings_manager.ts`, `faUserSettingsDefaults.ts`). Global keybind overrides: **`FA_KEYBINDS_IPC`**, `registerFaKeybindsIpc.ts`, `contentBridgeAPIs/faKeybindsAPI.ts` (renderer dispatch under `src/scripts/keybinds/`; [fantasia-keybinds](../skills/fantasia-keybinds/SKILL.md)). **`.faproject`** lifecycle/KV: **`FA_PROJECT_MANAGEMENT_IPC`**, **`registerFaProjectManagementIpc.ts`**, **`contentBridgeAPIs/projectManagementAPI.ts`**. Worlds/documents/templates/media CRUD + **Project Settings** list/snapshot: **`FA_PROJECT_CONTENT_IPC`**, **`registerFaProjectContentIpc.ts`**, **`contentBridgeAPIs/projectContentAPI.ts`** (contracts **`types/I_faProjectManagementDomain.ts`** / **`types/I_faProjectContentAPI.ts`**; main **`mainScripts/projectManagement/`** — [fantasia-sqlite-main](../skills/fantasia-sqlite-main/SKILL.md)).
- **IPC style (async first)**: Prefer `ipcMain.handle` + `ipcRenderer.invoke` + async preload APIs. Sync `sendSync`/blocking IPC last resort — avoid if any reasonable async design exists; document exceptions with short comment at handler or in review.
- **IPC payload validation (main)**: Structured `ipcMain.handle` data not trusted from TS types alone. Validate main with **Zod** (schemas under `src-electron/shared/`, e.g. `faUserSettingsPatchSchema.ts` in `registerFaUserSettingsIpc`). Strict object schemas + shared key sources (defaults modules) match cleanup/persistence. Single-arg scalars: `typeof` + domain helpers (e.g. external URL checks) when clearer than Zod.
- **IPC sender validation**: Handlers that mutate session or open OS resources verify **`event.sender.id`** matches the registered main window **`webContents`** (failsafe path reply, project OS-open, packaged DevTools guard). See [fantasia-electron-main](../skills/fantasia-electron-main/SKILL.md) **Security hardening**.
- Do not widen renderer `nodeIntegration` or expose raw `require`/`ipcRenderer` wholesale for shortcuts.
- `webPreferences.sandbox: true` → preload gets Electron-documented Node/`electron` subset only; no arbitrary npm in `contentBridgeAPIs/` — delegate path, `shell`, etc. to main via IPC (`electron-ipc-bridge.ts` + `register*Ipc`).
- Do **not** import **`neverthrow`** in **`contentBridgeAPIs/**`** (preload bundle). Prefer **`ipcRenderer.invoke(…).catch(…)`** + straightforward guards. **`src-electron/shared/**`** preload imports (**`faExternalUrlPredicate`**, etc.) stay **`neverthrow`-free**.
- Narrow typed methods; Vitest under `contentBridgeAPIs/_tests/` when behavior non-trivial.
- Comments/JSDoc in src-electron/: AGENTS.md rules (no Markdown emphasis; single quotes for symbol/path refs, not grave accents).
